On Thu, 30 Dec 1999, Stefan Mashkevich wrote:
> Please Cc: me <mash@mashke.org> as I'm not subscribed -- I'm afraid this
> is my last resort, with RTFM, reading archives, and 3 days of trying
> yielding nothing...
> 
> System: 2.2.13 installed on top of RH 6.1/Intel, Mitsumi CR-4802TE ATAPI
> CD-RW as master and Toshiba CD-ROM as slave on secondary IDE. With no SCSI
> emulation, the messages go like this:
> 
> Going the way suggested in cdrecord's README.ATAPI (disabling IDE CDROM
> support altogether and putting in SCSI emulation plus SCSI support) leads
> to kernel refusing to boot ("Ran out of input data").
When you did this, did you have CONFIG_BLK_DEV_SD as m, y, or is not
set?  If you have SD as m or y, that may have interfered with your set
up.
> So I go the way of the CD-Recording-HOWTO:
> 
> .config -->
> 
> CONFIG_BLK_DEV_IDE=y
> # CONFIG_BLK_DEV_HD_IDE is not set
> CONFIG_BLK_DEV_IDEDISK=y
> CONFIG_BLK_DEV_IDECD=m
> # CONFIG_BLK_DEV_IDETAPE is not set
> # CONFIG_BLK_DEV_IDEFLOPPY is not set
> CONFIG_BLK_DEV_IDESCSI=m
> <...>
> CONFIG_SCSI=y
> CONFIG_BLK_DEV_SD=m
> # CONFIG_CHR_DEV_ST is not set
> CONFIG_BLK_DEV_SR=m
> CONFIG_BLK_DEV_SR_VENDOR=y
> CONFIG_CHR_DEV_SG=m
> # CONFIG_SCSI_MULTI_LUN is not set
I've appended my configuration file for 2.2.13 which works for me.
Hopefully it will give you some help or suggestions.
> /etc/lilo.conf -->
> 
> append="hdc=noprobe hdc=ide-scsi hdd=ide-cd"
> 
> /etc/conf.modules -->
> 
> alias scd0 sr_mod
> alias scsi_hostadapter ide-scsi
> options ide-cd ignore=hdc
> 
> What happens is that the "hdc: ..." kernel message mentioned above 
> vanishes, BUT:
> 
> scsi : 0 hosts.
> scsi : detected total.
> and then
> 
> root[1002]:~# cdrecord -scanbus
> Cdrecord release 1.8a36 Copyright (C) 1995-1999 JÃ¶rg Schilling
> cdrecord: No such file or directory. Cannot open SCSI driver.
> 
> Compiling anything from the SCSI section into the kernel rather than
> modules doesn't help either. Also, taking ANY of the mentioned things out
> of lilo.conf or conf.modules (e.g. dropping hdc=noprobe from lilo.conf or
> commenting out the aliases in conf.modules) leads to the "hdc: ... "
> message reappearing, i.e., the CD-RW being grabbed by ide-cd. Which is
> also not the way the HOWTO, or the archives, indicate it should be.
There may be some interactions between ide cd support and ide scsi
support when both are available at the same time.  I've handled this a
couple of different ways.  
The first option involved compiling ide cd, ide scsi, and all the scsi
support as modular.  In this case I insmod ide cd support and both the
ide cdrom and cd rw drive function as normal ide devices.  The cdrom
gets seen as hdc and the cdrw drive is seen as hdd.  If I need to write
a cd I rmmod the ide cd support and insmod the ide scsi subsystem.  In
this case the ide cd drive gets seen as scd0 and the cd rw drive gets
seen as scd1.  
I've since rejected that in favor of the second option.  In this case I
disable ide cd support entirely.  Again, the cdrom drive is seen as scd0
and the cdrw is seen as scd1.  Everything gets compiled in as
monolithic, and I avoid the necessity of insmod/rmmod.  Symlinks for
/dev/cdrom and /dev/cdrw have to be adjusted accordingly, however.  
In neither case were the hdc=ide-cd or hdd=ide-scsi lines needed in
lilo.conf.  
